{"type":"message","id":"038101af","parentId":"7a7e4285","timestamp":"2026-04-15T21:05:42.425Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nice, we’ve got enough to start.\n\nWhat I confirmed:\n- Host is **Debian 12 (bookworm)** inside **WSL2**\n- OpenClaw is listening on:\n  - `*:18789`\n  - `127.0.0.1:33927`\n  - `127.0.0.1:18791`\n\nWhat I could not confirm cleanly:\n- `openclaw status`\n- `openclaw update status`\n- `openclaw security audit --deep`\n\nThose commands didn’t return promptly, so something may be off with the CLI responsiveness in this environment.\n\nMy take: before adding more functionality, the highest-value move is to stabilize and inspect the OpenClaw runtime itself.\n\nPick one:\n1. **diagnose OpenClaw status** first, recommended\n2. **set up automations/heartbeats/reminders**\n3. **set up messaging integrations**\n4. **create a custom input/workflow setup**\n5. **run a security and exposure review**\n\nI recommend **1** first, because if status/audit hangs, new setup work may be flaky too.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0beebb82725bec5a0169dffda2c79c819196ec0da62fe3274a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":113,"output":236,"cacheRead":16640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16989,"cost":{"input":0.00028250000000000004,"output":0.00354,"cacheRead":0.00416,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0079825}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776287137202,"responseId":"resp_0beebb82725bec5a0169dffda20e9c8191935c267b7771f0d0"}}
