{"type":"message","id":"036da22c","parentId":"88481649","timestamp":"2026-04-16T07:06:12.832Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes, and I verified it.\n\nWhat works:\n- `http://docling:5001/openapi.json` returns a valid OpenAPI spec\n- `http://docling:5001/docs` is available\n- the active conversion endpoint is:\n  - `http://docling:5001/v1/convert/file`\n\nWhat I tested:\n- I sent `test_research.txt` to `/v1/convert/file`\n- the service responded successfully, but **skipped the file**\n- reason: `File format not allowed: test_research.txt`\n\nSo the Docling service is reachable and callable, but this instance is configured to reject plain `.txt` uploads for conversion.\n\nIf you want, I can next:\n1. inspect which file types this Docling instance accepts\n2. try one of your PDF/DOCX/HTML-like files from the vault\n3. build a helper workflow that routes supported files to Docling automatically","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0beebb82725bec5a0169e08a5fe5688191ba29d33dd4bee505\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":273,"output":196,"cacheRead":21376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21845,"cost":{"input":0.0006825000000000001,"output":0.00294,"cacheRead":0.005344,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008966499999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776323166912,"responseId":"resp_0beebb82725bec5a0169e08a5ea8a081918c64202eae2951f7"}}
