{"type":"message","id":"a325cefd","parentId":"8a3d8afa","timestamp":"2026-04-16T07:12:30.097Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I’m going to inspect the source structure first so I can separate real Gemini conversations from the surrounding export noise, then I’ll write the cleaned markdown into `vault/Clean`.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0beebb82725bec5a0169e08bd4d95c8191a54774de404ce99f\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ude9droUobcbJmYZ4DAsjif9|fc_0beebb82725bec5a0169e08bdda6648191b2e92ee9641e8a48","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw/MyActivity.html')\ntext=p.read_text(errors='ignore')\nfor needle in ['Gemini Apps','Project Apollo','conversation','prompt','response','model','assistant']:\n    idx=text.lower().find(needle.lower())\n    print('NEEDLE', needle, 'IDX', idx)\n    if idx!=-1:\n        start=max(0, idx-500)\n        end=min(len(text), idx+1500)\n        print(text[start:end])\n        print('\\n'+'='*80+'\\n')\nPY","workdir":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":120},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python3 - <<'PY'\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\np=Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw/MyActivity.html')\\ntext=p.read_text(errors='ignore')\\nfor needle in ['Gemini Apps','Project Apollo','conversation','prompt','response','model','assistant']:\\n    idx=text.lower().find(needle.lower())\\n    print('NEEDLE', needle, 'IDX', idx)\\n    if idx!=-1:\\n        start=max(0, idx-500)\\n        end=min(len(text), idx+1500)\\n        print(text[start:end])\\n        print('\\\\n'+'='*80+'\\\\n')\\nPY\",\"workdir\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":120}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_u86q0ntmT4YgXyszSI5Svw7W|fc_0beebb82725bec5a0169e08bdda6848191bf1057aeb2372c89","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw/MyActivity.html')\nsoup=BeautifulSoup(p.read_text(errors='ignore'), 'html.parser')\nprint('title:', soup.title.string if soup.title else None)\nprint('h1 count:', len(soup.find_all('h1')))\nprint('h2 count:', len(soup.find_all('h2')))\nprint('tables:', len(soup.find_all('table')))\nprint('articles:', len(soup.find_all('article')))\nprint('divs:', len(soup.find_all('div')))\nfor tag in soup.find_all(['h1','h2','h3'])[:20]:\n    t=' '.join(tag.get_text(' ', strip=True).split())\n    if t:\n        print(tag.name, t[:200])\nPY","workdir":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":120},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python3 - <<'PY'\\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\np=Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw/MyActivity.html')\\nsoup=BeautifulSoup(p.read_text(errors='ignore'), 'html.parser')\\nprint('title:', soup.title.string if soup.title else None)\\nprint('h1 count:', len(soup.find_all('h1')))\\nprint('h2 count:', len(soup.find_all('h2')))\\nprint('tables:', len(soup.find_all('table')))\\nprint('articles:', len(soup.find_all('article')))\\nprint('divs:', len(soup.find_all('div')))\\nfor tag in soup.find_all(['h1','h2','h3'])[:20]:\\n    t=' '.join(tag.get_text(' ', strip=True).split())\\n    if t:\\n        print(tag.name, t[:200])\\nPY\",\"workdir\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":120}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":101,"output":484,"cacheRead":24192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24777,"cost":{"input":0.0002525,"output":0.00726,"cacheRead":0.0060479999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0135605}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776323540215,"responseId":"resp_0beebb82725bec5a0169e08bd41d5881918864635e1c7f47e5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"06b5fc43","parentId":"a325cefd","timestamp":"2026-04-16T07:12:30.430Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ude9droUobcbJmYZ4DAsjif9|fc_0beebb82725bec5a0169e08bdda6648191b2e92ee9641e8a48","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"NEEDLE Gemini Apps IDX 141904\nE;\n}\n\n.mdl-cell {\n  background-color: #FFFFFF;\n}\n\n.content-cell.mdl-cell {\n  color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54);\n}\n\n.header-cell.mdl-cell {\n  border-bottom-style: solid;\n  border-bottom-width: 1px;\n  border-bottom-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n}\n\n.image-preview {\n  width:72px;\n  height:72px;\n}\n\n</style></head><body><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"outer-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-shadow--2dp\"><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"header-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col\"><p class=\"mdl-typography--title\">Gemini Apps<br></p></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--6-col mdl-typography--body-1\">Prompted the docker is updated and the system is running, apparently\n\nhow do i use google takeout to export gemini conversations?<br>Apr 10, 2026, 10:25:57 PM EEST<br><p>To integrate your dispersed Gemini research into the <strong>Apollo Intelligence Engine</strong>, you will use Google Takeout as your primary &quot;Data Extraction Rig.&quot; Because Google separates different types of AI data, following these specific steps is crucial to ensure you capture the actual conversation transcripts rather than just metadata.</p>\n<h3>1. The Google Takeout Extraction SOP</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Access the Portal</strong>: Navigate to <a href=\"https://takeout.google.com\">takeout.google.com</a>. Ensure you are logged into the account containing your Project Apollo research.</li>\n<li><strong>Clear the Deck</strong>: Click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong> at the top of the list to avoid downloading gigabytes of unnecessary data.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;Gems&quot; Layer</strong>: Scroll down and check the box for <strong>&quot;Gemini&quot;</strong>. This exports your custom Gemini &quot;Gems&quot; configurations.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;History&quot; Layer (Critical Step)</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to <strong>&quot;My Activity&quot;</strong> and check the box.</li>\n<li>Click the button labeled <strong>&quot;All activity data included&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li>In the pop-up, c\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE Project Apollo IDX 142751\nce Engine</strong>, you will use Google Takeout as your primary &quot;Data Extraction Rig.&quot; Because Google separates different types of AI data, following these specific steps is crucial to ensure you capture the actual conversation transcripts rather than just metadata.</p>\n<h3>1. The Google Takeout Extraction SOP</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Access the Portal</strong>: Navigate to <a href=\"https://takeout.google.com\">takeout.google.com</a>. Ensure you are logged into the account containing your Project Apollo research.</li>\n<li><strong>Clear the Deck</strong>: Click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong> at the top of the list to avoid downloading gigabytes of unnecessary data.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;Gems&quot; Layer</strong>: Scroll down and check the box for <strong>&quot;Gemini&quot;</strong>. This exports your custom Gemini &quot;Gems&quot; configurations.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;History&quot; Layer (Critical Step)</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to <strong>&quot;My Activity&quot;</strong> and check the box.</li>\n<li>Click the button labeled <strong>&quot;All activity data included&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li>In the pop-up, click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong>, then scroll down and check <strong>ONLY &quot;Gemini Apps&quot;</strong>. Click <strong>&quot;OK&quot;</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Finalize Export</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll to the bottom and click <strong>&quot;Next step&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li><strong>Delivery Method</strong>: Choose &quot;Send download link via email&quot;.</li>\n<li><strong>File Type</strong>: Select <strong>.zip</strong> for maximum compatibility with your local workstation.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>&quot;Create export&quot;</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<h3>2. Processing the Payload for Apollo</h3>\n<p>Once your export arrives (usually within minutes to a few hours), you will receive a ZIP file.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Locating the Data</strong>: Inside the ZIP, navigate to <code>Takeout &gt; My Activity\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE conversation IDX 142118\ngba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n}\n\n.image-preview {\n  width:72px;\n  height:72px;\n}\n\n</style></head><body><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"outer-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-shadow--2dp\"><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"header-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col\"><p class=\"mdl-typography--title\">Gemini Apps<br></p></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--6-col mdl-typography--body-1\">Prompted the docker is updated and the system is running, apparently\n\nhow do i use google takeout to export gemini conversations?<br>Apr 10, 2026, 10:25:57 PM EEST<br><p>To integrate your dispersed Gemini research into the <strong>Apollo Intelligence Engine</strong>, you will use Google Takeout as your primary &quot;Data Extraction Rig.&quot; Because Google separates different types of AI data, following these specific steps is crucial to ensure you capture the actual conversation transcripts rather than just metadata.</p>\n<h3>1. The Google Takeout Extraction SOP</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Access the Portal</strong>: Navigate to <a href=\"https://takeout.google.com\">takeout.google.com</a>. Ensure you are logged into the account containing your Project Apollo research.</li>\n<li><strong>Clear the Deck</strong>: Click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong> at the top of the list to avoid downloading gigabytes of unnecessary data.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;Gems&quot; Layer</strong>: Scroll down and check the box for <strong>&quot;Gemini&quot;</strong>. This exports your custom Gemini &quot;Gems&quot; configurations.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;History&quot; Layer (Critical Step)</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to <strong>&quot;My Activity&quot;</strong> and check the box.</li>\n<li>Click the button labeled <strong>&quot;All activity data included&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li>In the pop-up, click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong>, then scroll down and check <strong>ONLY &quot;Gemini Apps&quot;</strong>. Click <strong>&quot;OK&quot;</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Finalize Export</strong>\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE prompt IDX 142003\n.54);\n}\n\n.header-cell.mdl-cell {\n  border-bottom-style: solid;\n  border-bottom-width: 1px;\n  border-bottom-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n}\n\n.image-preview {\n  width:72px;\n  height:72px;\n}\n\n</style></head><body><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"outer-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-shadow--2dp\"><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"header-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col\"><p class=\"mdl-typography--title\">Gemini Apps<br></p></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--6-col mdl-typography--body-1\">Prompted the docker is updated and the system is running, apparently\n\nhow do i use google takeout to export gemini conversations?<br>Apr 10, 2026, 10:25:57 PM EEST<br><p>To integrate your dispersed Gemini research into the <strong>Apollo Intelligence Engine</strong>, you will use Google Takeout as your primary &quot;Data Extraction Rig.&quot; Because Google separates different types of AI data, following these specific steps is crucial to ensure you capture the actual conversation transcripts rather than just metadata.</p>\n<h3>1. The Google Takeout Extraction SOP</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Access the Portal</strong>: Navigate to <a href=\"https://takeout.google.com\">takeout.google.com</a>. Ensure you are logged into the account containing your Project Apollo research.</li>\n<li><strong>Clear the Deck</strong>: Click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong> at the top of the list to avoid downloading gigabytes of unnecessary data.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;Gems&quot; Layer</strong>: Scroll down and check the box for <strong>&quot;Gemini&quot;</strong>. This exports your custom Gemini &quot;Gems&quot; configurations.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;History&quot; Layer (Critical Step)</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to <strong>&quot;My Activity&quot;</strong> and check the box.</li>\n<li>Click the button labeled <strong>&quot;All activity data included&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li>In the pop-up, click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong>, then scroll down and check <strong>ONLY &quot;Gemin\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE response IDX 145184\nn the &quot;Incremental Indexing&quot; process, mapping the relationships between these historical conversations and your current architectural decisions.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3>3. Alternative: &quot;Surgical&quot; Export for High-Value Threads</h3>\n<p>If you have a single, long conversation that is foundational to your <strong>Remote Viewing (RV)</strong> or <strong>Biohacking</strong> protocols, the Takeout JSON/HTML can sometimes be messy.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Export to Docs</strong>: Under any response in Gemini, click the three dots (<strong>⋮</strong>) and select <strong>&quot;Export to Docs&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li><strong>Conversion</strong>: Save that Google Doc as a <code>.md</code> or <code>.txt</code> file and move it to your <code>C:/Apollo/Vault/Inputs</code> folder. This often preserves formatting better than the bulk Takeout method.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Operational Tip</strong>: After indexing, ask your &quot;Strategist&quot; (Gemma 26B) to &quot;Identify all duplicated research concepts in the newly ingested Gemini logs.&quot; This will help you prune the &quot;noise&quot; and finalize your master project ledger.</p>\n<p>Does the system appear to be indexing the initial <code>.txt</code> files in your Vault correctly, or should we verify the LightRAG connection?</p>\n<br></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--6-col mdl-typography--body-1 mdl-typography--text-right\"></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-typography--caption\"><b>Products:</b><br>&emsp;Gemini Apps<br><b>Why is this here?</b><br>&emsp;This activity was saved to your Google Account because the following settings were on:&nbsp;Gemini Apps Activity.&nbsp;You can control these settings &nbsp;<a href=\"https://myaccount.google.com/activitycontrols\">here</a>.</div></div></div><div class=\"outer-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-shadow--2dp\"><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"header-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col\"><p class=\"mdl-typography--title\">Gemini Apps<br></p><\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE model IDX 150082\ncode>.</li>\n<li>Install the <strong>Dataview</strong> and <strong>Tracker</strong> plugins as recommended.</li>\n<li>Create a &quot;Master Ledger&quot; note with a simple query to list all files indexed in the last 24 hours to verify everything was ingested.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<h3>3. The &quot;Council of AIs&quot; Synthesis</h3>\n<p>With the data indexed, you can now use <strong>Open WebUI</strong> to run a &quot;Council Debate&quot; via the <strong>MCP protocol</strong>. This allows the models to &quot;read&quot; the synthesized knowledge base directly.</p>\n<p><strong>Try this &quot;Golden Query&quot; to test the system&#39;s integration:</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&quot;Review all ingested research files and identify any architectural contradictions between the Remote Viewing (RV) protocol and our Health/Biohacking module. Synthesize a single &#39;Sovereign Consensus&#39; document that resolves these gaps.&quot;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3>4. VRAM Management Check</h3>\n<p>Running <strong>Gemma 4 26B (Strategist)</strong> alongside these new services will be tight.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strategy</strong>: Use the <code>apollo_up.bat</code> script to prioritize services. During the &quot;Ingestion Phase,&quot; you can keep the models in <strong>CPU-only mode</strong> or use a smaller model like <strong>Qwen 9B (Scout)</strong> for indexing to keep the 16GB VRAM free for the final synthesis.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Would you like me to draft a quick Python script for the <code>apollo-agent</code> to automate the conversion of your loose text files into the structured Markdown format that LightRAG prefers?</strong></p>\n<br></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--6-col mdl-typography--body-1 mdl-typography--text-right\"></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-typography--caption\"><b>Products:</b><br>&emsp;Gemini Apps<br><b>Why is this here?</b><br>&emsp;This activity was saved to your Google Account because the following settings were on:&\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE assistant IDX 172646\nork access.\nOllama: Managing a model fleet (Gemma 4 26B Strategist, Ministral 14B Architect, Qwen 9B Scout).\nOpen WebUI: Primary human-interface for chat and documentation.\nSidecars: browserless (scraping), docling (PDF/Doc ingestion), and Whisper V3 Turbo (audio ears).\n2. Current Project Scope (Non-Physics Focus)\nWhile the long-term goal involves Causal Signatures, the current priority is the Technical Utility Phase. The following modules require immediate development:\n\nPersonal Research &amp; Assistantship: Configuring OpenClaw to act as a high-authority research librarian. This includes indexing the local &quot;Vault&quot; and &quot;Intel&quot; directories for instant retrieval and synthesis of multi-source data.\nInventory &amp; Resource Management: Building a systematic tracking method for physical and digital assets, likely utilizing a structured JSON or Markdown-based ledger within the local workspace.\nHealth &amp; Biohacking: Structuring the ingestion of biometric data and medical literature. The goal is to provide evidence-based insights into personal health optimization through the &quot;Strategist&quot; model.\nRemote Viewing (RV) Logic: Designing a &quot;Blind Monitor&quot; protocol. This requires configuring a restricted information flow where the AI acts as a monitor, holding target metadata securely and only validating the viewer’s session data post-hoc.\n3. Operational Constraints\nPrivacy First: All processing is 100% local. No data should be sent to external APIs unless explicitly requested for &quot;World Web&quot; searching.\nVRAM Ceiling: Total VRAM is 16GB. The system must manage model swaps efficiently to avoid OOM (Out of Memory) crashes during high-density research sessions.\nSovereign Logic: The user operates as the Architect; the AI operates as the Executive Partner. Every technical change must be documented in a local project log.\n4. Immediate Action Items for the New Instance\nSkill Refinement: Finalizing the OpenClaw &quot;Plugins&quot; config\n\n================================================================================"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":302,"aggregated":"NEEDLE Gemini Apps IDX 141904\nE;\n}\n\n.mdl-cell {\n  background-color: #FFFFFF;\n}\n\n.content-cell.mdl-cell {\n  color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54);\n}\n\n.header-cell.mdl-cell {\n  border-bottom-style: solid;\n  border-bottom-width: 1px;\n  border-bottom-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n}\n\n.image-preview {\n  width:72px;\n  height:72px;\n}\n\n</style></head><body><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"outer-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-shadow--2dp\"><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"header-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col\"><p class=\"mdl-typography--title\">Gemini Apps<br></p></div><div class=\"content-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--6-col mdl-typography--body-1\">Prompted the docker is updated and the system is running, apparently\n\nhow do i use google takeout to export gemini conversations?<br>Apr 10, 2026, 10:25:57 PM EEST<br><p>To integrate your dispersed Gemini research into the <strong>Apollo Intelligence Engine</strong>, you will use Google Takeout as your primary &quot;Data Extraction Rig.&quot; Because Google separates different types of AI data, following these specific steps is crucial to ensure you capture the actual conversation transcripts rather than just metadata.</p>\n<h3>1. The Google Takeout Extraction SOP</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Access the Portal</strong>: Navigate to <a href=\"https://takeout.google.com\">takeout.google.com</a>. Ensure you are logged into the account containing your Project Apollo research.</li>\n<li><strong>Clear the Deck</strong>: Click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong> at the top of the list to avoid downloading gigabytes of unnecessary data.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;Gems&quot; Layer</strong>: Scroll down and check the box for <strong>&quot;Gemini&quot;</strong>. This exports your custom Gemini &quot;Gems&quot; configurations.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;History&quot; Layer (Critical Step)</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to <strong>&quot;My Activity&quot;</strong> and check the box.</li>\n<li>Click the button labeled <strong>&quot;All activity data included&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li>In the pop-up, c\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE Project Apollo IDX 142751\nce Engine</strong>, you will use Google Takeout as your primary &quot;Data Extraction Rig.&quot; Because Google separates different types of AI data, following these specific steps is crucial to ensure you capture the actual conversation transcripts rather than just metadata.</p>\n<h3>1. The Google Takeout Extraction SOP</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Access the Portal</strong>: Navigate to <a href=\"https://takeout.google.com\">takeout.google.com</a>. Ensure you are logged into the account containing your Project Apollo research.</li>\n<li><strong>Clear the Deck</strong>: Click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong> at the top of the list to avoid downloading gigabytes of unnecessary data.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;Gems&quot; Layer</strong>: Scroll down and check the box for <strong>&quot;Gemini&quot;</strong>. This exports your custom Gemini &quot;Gems&quot; configurations.</li>\n<li><strong>The &quot;History&quot; Layer (Critical Step)</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to <strong>&quot;My Activity&quot;</strong> and check the box.</li>\n<li>Click the button labeled <strong>&quot;All activity data included&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li>In the pop-up, click <strong>&quot;Deselect all&quot;</strong>, then scroll down and check <strong>ONLY &quot;Gemini Apps&quot;</strong>. Click <strong>&quot;OK&quot;</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Finalize Export</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll to the bottom and click <strong>&quot;Next step&quot;</strong>.</li>\n<li><strong>Delivery Method</strong>: Choose &quot;Send download link via email&quot;.</li>\n<li><strong>File Type</strong>: Select <strong>.zip</strong> for maximum compatibility with your local workstation.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>&quot;Create export&quot;</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<h3>2. Processing the Payload for Apollo</h3>\n<p>Once your export arrives (usually within minutes to a few hours), you will receive a ZIP file.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Locating the Data</strong>: Inside the ZIP, navigate to <code>Takeout &gt; My Activity\n\n================================================================================\n\nNEEDLE conversation IDX 142118\ngba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n}\n\n.image-preview {\n  width:72px;\n  height:72px;\n}\n\n</style></head><body><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"outer-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col mdl-shadow--2dp\"><div class=\"mdl-grid\"><div class=\"header-cell mdl-cell mdl-cell--